{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, task-specific fine-tuning is expected to produce better performance on the particular task the model was tuned to, so it might be the method of choice if there is a single downstream task and if sufficient labelled data is available.",
    "These two fine-tuning approaches are explored in turn.",
    "Domain-specific fine-tuning can be achieved by applying the model to a \"masked language modelling\" task.",
    "This involves taking a sentence, randomly masking a certain percentage of the words in the input, and then running the entire masked sentence through the model, which has to predict the masked words.",
    "This self-supervised approach is an automated process to generate inputs and labels from the texts and does not require any human labelling."
  ]
}